description: This Mexican-inspired taco recipe is a flavour-packed punch of green salsa, orange, slaw and prawns that's ready in 20 minutes. Make tonight taco night.
keywords: Taco,Low saturated fat,Low salt,Prawn,Gluten free,Tree nut free,Healthier Easier,Low sugar,Summer,High protein,High fibre,Soy free,Wheat free,Kale,Tomato,Peanut free
name: DIY Prawn Tacos With Green Salsa Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat a barbecue or grill pan on high heat and brush lightly with oil. Grill prawns for 3 minutes each side or until charred and cooked through. Set aside.
To make green salsa, combine 1/2 bunch parsley, 1/2 bunch basil, 2 cloves of garlic, olive oil and lemon juice in a small bowl. Season with pepper.
Fill taco shells with prawns, corn, kale slaw, avocado and orange segments. Top with green salsa.
